    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Thanks for the suggestion @Ro5s. We use private variables so that we can have tighter control in the way that the values are modified. For example, we can guarantee that balances and total supply in ERC20 are modified together, and that this modification emits an event. This is not something we're willing to change currently.\r\n\r\nTo access these values you should be able to use the functions of the contract. To customize these values you can generally use inheritance and overriding.",
